messages.message:
Hi Team, I've had to create a document for our AI Hub language support for a prospect. Would it make sense to add this/something like this to our AI Hub Doc Centre?

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ARqsGJzBsnahZiGOjVn7UymGNX7uTspm2kSRR0-9_Ww/edit

List based off of this:

https://botpress.com/blog/list-of-languages-supported-by-chatgpt

I like this! But I worry about maintainability. Would it make sense to link out instead to OpenAI documentation on this?

And what exactly do we mean by “support”? Do we mean you can ask questions in any of these languages? Translate to all of these languages? For example, the first result I found in OpenAI listed a bunch of languages that are supported for their transcription and translation endpoints.
